[SN]TITLE[SN]
Distiller sought for distillery on Isle of Raasay

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A distiller is being sought for one of Scotland's newest and remotest distilleries.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
R&B Distillers is turning Borodale House, a derelict Victorian hotel on the Isle of Raasay, into a distillery and visitor centre.
Getting to the island, which has a population of about 120 people, involves a ferry journey from Skye.
The job description includes formal qualifications and experience and a willingness to live on an island.
The production of the first whisky at the site could begin in April next year.
